track_notes: This is a nice summit, quite easy to walk! You must not come here in winter time, for the place is a busy ski resort; unless you can ski and activate in the cold
This way to Mont ST Sauveur is the harder, because you have to clim more than 2000m up! the place is wide of antenna, and you can park next to the bridge easy.

Do not try this path in winter, the place is a ski resort. in summer you can use the free telecabine if you are a bit lazy. The walk is not difficult but you need water and good shoes. plenty room for antenna on summit.
Not in winter time, unless you are a good skiman!

Nice walk to the summit, not in winter time unless you are good on ski. The path is easy, you need good shoes. The panorama is wonderfull. There is plenty room for antennas on summit. More info @ F6HBI
Not in wintertime as this is a ski resort
